    In Ce: (Type M) (From External Customer Hugh McCutchen, Jr.)
    create a command file with the following lines in buffer t1:
    es 'This i a long line which is the first line of the file';en
    es 'this is line 2 and it is intermediate length';en
    es 'and this is a short line'
    define:   kd ^1 cmdf -p t1 ke
    edit a new file with:
    ce -w  -cmd "ei -off" /tmp/zblabbo
    use ^1 to add the three lines.  Move the cursor under the i in "file"
    on the first line.  Begin pressing backspace.  Make sure that nothing
    get magically pasted when the backspace crosses line the end of line 2.

    In Ce: (Type O)
    Where neither /tmp/z nor $HOME/z exist:
    ce /tmp/z
    ce $HOME/z
    Make sure you do not get a false cc window detection

    In ceterm (Type O)
    Especially to an HP
    remsh numenor /projects/ce/hpux10/ceterm -display desoto:0
    Make sure the pseudo terminal opens correctly and the pseudo
    terminal name does not end up in the transcript pad.  For Boeing.

    In Ce: (Type D)
    1. Create a file with a tab followed by text, E.G.
   	aaaa
       Make sure there is enough data to fill the screen so you can
       scroll down.
    2. ca some text, E.G. the middle two a's.
    3. Scroll down and then back up.  Make sure the color is set
       up correctly.
    4. Add enough lines above the colored line to push it off the
       screen.  Now cut those lines and make sure the color is ok
       when the line returns.  Make sure line 1 is not deleted,
       thus causing a partial redraw.

    In Ceterm (Type D)
    create_data 16384 1
    With scroll bars on.
    Make sure the horizontal scroll bar works.

    In Ce (Type D)
    In any file, on one line.  Color 2 words red.  Then color
    two later words in the same line blue.  Make sure the red
    does not go away.  Execute "debug color", then add a bit of
    green completely contained in the blue area.  Then type some
    data in the green area.  Execute "debug color" and make sure the
    blue area is split.

    In Ce (Type X)
    Run the following commands, make sure the cursor does not find the
    red on line 5.
    5,6ca red
    5ca blue
    1nc red   # Error is: currsor goes to line 5 even though it is no longer red
    1nc blue  # also goes to line 5.
    Then press Return (tr;en) on the blue line,  The newly created
    line should be the default colors.

    In Ce (Type D)
    Try to make the window real small. Make sure it will not let you
    get too small.

    In Ce (Type X)
    Open a file and do an xc. Then create a cc window.  In the cc window,
    do an xc and then close the first window.  Go to a different
    window and do an xc.  Try to paste in the original cc window.
    Make sure the correct data gets processed.

    In ceterm (Type X)
    Open a new ceterm. ceterm -geo 500x500-1+1
    Do an "again" on line zero, the empty first line in the transcript
    pad.  Do a pwd in the UNIX window and press enter.  Then
    go to line zero in the transcript pad and try to do an again
    on the pwd command.  Make sure the pwd is transfered.  The
    problem was the area to the left of the cursor was transfered.

    In Ce (Type D)
    Execute:
    [7,1];dr;[15,9] ca red blue
    [20,5]dr;[20,15] ca yellow green
    kd BackSpace ee -w ke
    On the line above the yellow/green, do line deletes until the
    line moves up.  Make sure the color moves properly.
    Undo and repeat using BackSpace to the left of the green area.
    Make sure the color moves up one line properly.
  
    in ceterm (Type D)
    With scroll bar mode set to auto.
    do a few ls's to fill the screen and have the horizontal scroll bar
    off.  Then do a phone command or something with will generate wide
    output.  Make sure the scroll bar is not covering the last line
    of data when it turns on.


