    in Ce (Tupe D)
    In scroll bar mode auto.  If you do a ^b (pb;tb;tr) and the
    horizontal scroll bar is off in the current window and on
    in the window at the bottom of the file, the last line should not
    get covered up by the scroll bar.


    In Ce (Type D)
    Open a file and do a cc
    make changes in one window.
    undo the changes.  Make sure the M flag goes
    off in the cc window at the same time as in the main window.


    In ceterm (Type D)
    put window in NP9 position.
    sb -auto
    Do an ls -la in the crpad directory so the horizontal scroll
    bar shows up.  Then do 3 pwd's.  Go to the main pad
    and scroll up (pp 0.5) twice.  The scroll bar should go away
    on the second scroll.  Problem was window scrolled incorrectly.
   

    In Ce (Type S)
    In aegis mode:
    Run "s/@n@t{[~>]}/ @1/"
    Over the following data:
    Col 1 (note col 1 has a tab in it)
    |
    V
    	> > condition is considered to be advanced and, thus, yesterday I began
    	my
    	first
    	> > day of chemotherapy treatment.
    	> >
    	> > I will undergo chemotherapy for at least nine weeks and then,
    	depending on


    In Ce (Type S)
    In aegis mode:
    Run "s/@[{?*}@]/ PRED(@1)]/"
    Over the following data:
    Col 1
    |
    V
    Here's the contents of the file.
    The command was run on the line indicated below with '>'.
        [i_inactive2_t312_timer]     := VALUE ( 
            [FIRST(bri_secondary_timer_type_sbr)..
    >       [i_t312_timer]     := VALUE ( 
            [i_t312_timer]     := VALUE ( 
            [i_t312_timer]     := VALUE ( 
             LAST(bri_secondary_timer_type_sbr)] := invalid_bri_secondary_timer_start_translation
    The error was a memory fault.


    In Ce (Type S)
    In aegis mode,  Make sure
    1,$s/<?a>//
    works on lines that end in '</a>'

    In ceterm (must use ceterm) (Type S) (Promoted to be done earlier, was just below 2.2)
