    In Ce (Type U)
    Make a few changes in a file (delete some lines).
    Save the file out, the 'M' box goes away.
    Make a change and them 'M' box comes back.
    Do an undo and the 'M' box stays even though the
    file now matches what is on the disk.  Undo back to
    the beginning and the 'M' box goes away even though
    the memory image no longer matches what is on the
    disk.

    In Ce (Type U)
    Set up the following key definition.  Edit a test file.
    Run the key.  Make sure it does not memory fault.
    kd ^1 undo;es'12345';redo;undo;undo;es'12345';redo ke


    In Ce (Type S) (Failed at 2.5 & 2.5.1 & 2.5.2)
    in unix mode
    s/[^x]/x/ caused infinite loop on any line
    Try on a line with and x and also without.


