    In Ce (Type X)
    Execute the following line on a line at least 50 characters
    long:
    [7,1],[7,9]ca red blue;[7,21],[7,23]ca red blue;[7,36],[7,39]ca red blue;
    Split the line in the middle of the center colored section.
    Undo. Redo.  Go to the end of the first line which just got
    split.  Do a character delete to rejoin the lines.  Make sure
    the color looks the same.  Do the same in the last colored
    area.
    Split the line just after the last character of the first
    colored area. The start of the new line should not be colored.
    Move right two characters on the new line and split the line.
    The two characters on a line by themselves should not change
    color. Grab a bunch of lines into a paste buffer and paste
    them at the begining, middle, and end of a colored region.
    Also, just before and after.  Make sure the results are as
    expected.
    Undo the changes back to the original line being colored.
    Split at the middle of the center colored section.  Delete
    with 'ed' the newline at the end of the line to rejoin.  Do
    this 3 times. Split one more time.  This time move the cursor
    a few characters to the right of the newline and do 'ed'.
    This does a join with padding.  Repeat substituting a cut
    (xd) for the delete (ed).

