    in Ceterm (Type E)
    Compile the following program:
    #include <stdio.h>   /* /usr/include/stdio.h  */
    #include <string.h>  /* /usr/include/string.h */
    main(int argc, char *argv[])
    {
    char      buff[80][1024];
    int       count = 0;
    int       i;

    while(gets(buff[count++]) != NULL)
    ; /* just read into the buffer */

    sleep(2);
    for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
      puts(buff[i]);
    } /* end of main */
    Run the program in a ceterm window.  Enter two or three
    lines and then press ^d for eof.  The program should wait
    the two seconds and echo out the lines typed in.  The bug
    was that the lines were not echoed until you move the
    cursor or caused some X event.  Do not enter more than 80
    lines.

