    In ce  (Type S & C & D)
    Verify the correction of the following substitute bugs.
    - s/ /xy/ does not replace all blanks 
          where xy is any 2 or more characters replacement string.
    - if s/str1/str2/ fails because str1 is not in range,
         cursor should go to character after the end of the marked range.
    - if s/str1/str2/ suceeds because str1 is in range,
         cursor should go to last char of str2 instead of after str1 like DM.
    - Inserting characters in a paragraph in word wrap mode causes
      chunks of text to be repeated on the next line.
    - Semicolon not allowed in: kd ^1;
    - Space after ^1 causes message about incomplete definition:
      kd m3 ;
    - a prompt in &'prompt' that won't fit in the command line causes
      the window to jump to the upper left hand side of the screen
      and causes to Motif border to go off the screen so that the window
      can't be manipulated with the mouse.
 

