    in ce (type P),
    kd bs should define the shifted b and not <BackSpace> per the discussion below.
       kd bs ?  does that define <BackSpace>, how do i define key <b. shifted?
       -  bs will define the <backspace key>, bss will define the backspace key
          shifted.
          You are right, Bs should define shifted B, but defines bs since the
          Apollo keynames are treated non-case sensitive.
          If we want to do something about this, we better make it before R1 or
          we will be locked in with keydefs which get written.
      -   Solution,  kd bs has been removed as a special apollo case.

