    The null lines should get pasted.

    upon invocation, if mouse cursor is not in edit window and any
    key is hit, a core dump is taken. This is for a machine with
    explicit pointer focus.

    after mouse cursor has been in window, if it is moved out and
    text typed, the first character appears at line 0 (no kidding),
    and subsequent text is inserted at a vertical displacement equal
    to that of the mouse cursor when it was outside the window. THis
    is for a machine with explicit pointer focus.

    if an area is highlighted, and the cursor is put in the Command:
    window, and backspace is pressed into the left margin, the
    highlight is lost, until the mouse cursor is moved into the text
    area, at which point the original end-of-highlight-area point is
    lost

    '//' (repeat search) dumps if no previous pattern (unless at eof), and
    '\\' (backward search) dumps if no previous pattern (unless at bof)

    /@@/ should find an at sign.

    Go into a file.  somewhere in the middle of a line
    type abc.  then press <esc> (tdm) and do \abc\.
    The new text should be found.

    
